Now we have comments from both authors.

Summary:
- LablGL is type-safe, CamlGL is not.
- LablGL support OGL 1.1, CamlGL support OGL 1.4 with extensions (most=20
important: shaders [NV,ATI,ARB]).
- LablGL support GLU 1.2, CamlGL has no GLU support.
- LablGL is better for beginners, CamlGL is better for people with prior =
OGL=20
knowledge.
- LablGL uses Raw module, CamlGL uses Bigarray.
- LablGL support all Ocaml platforms, CamlGL support only Windows (VC) an=
d=20
Linux.
- LablGL is better tested.

